BENIN – Aminu Waziri Tam­buwal, the Sokoto State Governor has warned his party members, the Peoples Dem­ocratic Party (PDP), not to cast their ballots on the ba­sis of primordial sentiments during the forthcoming na­tional convention of the par­ty but should choose the aspi­rant with the best credentials as party flag bearer for 2023. Tambuwal, who is desir­ous of succeeding President Muhammadu Buhari in 2023 on the ticket of PDP made the call while campaigning to the national delegates of the par­ty in Edo State at the party secretariat in Benin City on Friday. Going down memory lane, he described himself as the most qualified in terms of legislative and executive ex­perience among all those that have so far signified inten­tion to vie for the Presidency in 2023. -Advertisement- He promised his audience that he will make good use of his chain of experience to give financial autonomy to the judiciary, the legislative and the local government councils. Referring to his achieve­ments as governor of Soko­to State where primary edu­cation has been made fully free and accessible to all and sundry, he promised that he will replicate it at the centre. On restructuring of the country, he stated that he is in full support of it and would endeavour to implement it, adding that under his watch no part of the country will be left behind in the scheme of things.